record_data.record_plain_text: PANTHER CREEK POWER OPERATING, LLC REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCE SERVICE Panther Creek Power Operating, LLC ("Panther Creek") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power Service") from its electric generation facility located in Nesquehoning, Pennsylvania ("Panther Creek Facility") to PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). In this Tariff for Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources, Panther Creek hereby sets forth its revenue requirements for the Panther Creek Facility's provision of Reactive Power Service, pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. This Rate Schedule shall be effective September 1, 2022 pursuant to Panther Creek Power Operating, LLC, 180 FERC 61,152, at P 4 (2022). Panther Creek's monthly revenue requirements below consist of charges for the Fixed Capability Component. Total charges for any 12-month period shall not be less than those specified below. Revenue Requirements: Fixed Capability Component The total annual revenue requirement = $160,000 The total monthly revenue requirement = $13,333.33 [$160,000/12]
